		       The Good Life		        		        
		       </div>
          <h3 class="entry-title"><a href="http://mimithorisson.com/2017/12/19/fruits-dautomne/" rel="bookmark">Fruits d&#8217;Automne</a></h3>
          <!-- <h4 class="vcard author">by <span class="fn">mimithorisson</span></h4> -->
          
          <div class="entry-content">

              <p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mimikaki.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-6555" src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mimikaki-710x536.jpg" alt="" width="710" height="536" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mimikaki-710x536.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mimikaki-300x226.jpg 300w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mimikaki-768x580.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px" /></a></p>
<p><strong>The Fruits of fall and vegetables of winter</strong></p>
<p>A few weeks ago, on a Sunday, the girls were playing rough in their room and broke an old chair they used for their desk. A pity as it was a nice chair &#8230; but these things happen. Fortunately, about the easiest thing to replace in our village on a Sunday is a desk chair. In M√©doc nothing is open on Sundays and our village and the surrounding ones literally have no stores at all. All we have is an antiques store, full of little gems. And the best part is, it‚Äôs open on Sunday afternoons. In other words, in our neck of the woods you couldn‚Äôt buy diapers or shampoo to save your life on a Sunday but a new chandelier or a portrait of someone‚Äôs grandfather, not a problem. After lunch Oddur headed to St Christoly and came back with two chairs (what‚Äôs happened once can always happen again, right?) some nice decanters and a beautiful drawing of a lady holding a basket of apples. Under it, in Italics, is written : Fruits d‚ÄôAutomne. Next to the sentence is a drawing of a funny little man with a hat. I was immediately taken by the image, very nicely done, very carefree, very seasonal. Seasonal before it became a lifestyle, when it was simply life. I immediately decided to talk about the lady in the picture in my next blogpost ‚Äì the timing was just so perfect, but she also made me think about our way of life. Now that we have lived in the countryside for 7 years, seasonal living has truly become a part of who I am and while I can still remember how it was living in Paris (and it was magical) I can‚Äôt really feel it. We cook with what we have and what we have is what‚Äôs in season. Writing a blog over a period of time, I‚Äôm sure I‚Äôm starting to repeat myself, thoughts much like fruits and vegetables are cyclical, but just like you can never eat the same apple twice ‚Äì neither can a thought ever be exactly the same. We all feel a familiar feeling as Christmas approaches, we go through the same motions. Buying presents, setting up the Christmas tree, the old ornaments. Stocking up on Champagne, planning feasts. But something is always new, even if it‚Äôs just our own perspective &#8230; and in our case we usually have a new family member pretty much every year.</p>
<p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/salad.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-6556" src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/salad-710x536.jpg" alt="" width="710" height="536" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/salad-710x536.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/salad-300x226.jpg 300w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/salad-768x580.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/ladywithapples.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-6557" src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/ladywithapples-710x536.jpg" alt="" width="710" height="536" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/ladywithapples-710x536.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/ladywithapples-300x226.jpg 300w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/ladywithapples-768x580.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/jartichokes.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-6558" src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/jartichokes-710x536.jpg" alt="" width="710" height="536" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/jartichokes-710x536.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/jartichokes-300x226.jpg 300w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/jartichokes-768x580.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mimigirls.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-6559" src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mimigirls-710x536.jpg" alt="" width="710" height="536" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mimigirls-710x536.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mimigirls-300x226.jpg 300w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mimigirls-768x580.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/kitchenandkaki.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-6560" src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/kitchenandkaki-710x536.jpg" alt="" width="710" height="536" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/kitchenandkaki-710x536.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/kitchenandkaki-300x226.jpg 300w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/kitchenandkaki-768x580.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px" /></a></p>
<p>This time I decided to do a very approachable menu, nothing too fancy, very tried and tested in this house. I think we‚Äôve had all the dishes at least 5 times in the last few weeks. The ingredients are all quite humble, but of great quality and as it happens, very healthy. Kakis are some of my absolute favourite fruits and while I usually just have them plain after a big meal, when a light dessert is required, they are also wonderful in fritters. Talking about new thoughts, I was recently in Torino doing a special blend with our friends from the Vergnano coffee family in Chieri and one night we had dinner at the wonderful Al Gatto Nero restaurant. After indulging too much in white truffles, Andrea, the brilliant owner, who to me IS the place, suggested something light, Kaki. The way they served it was lightly soaked in Rum with a tiny dollop of ice-cream in the middle. It was as perfect an ending to a meal as any I‚Äôve had.</p>
<p>The salad was the first thing on the menu and the first thing I thought of. We‚Äôve been enjoying it so much recently and a dear friend, Hrafnhildur from Iceland, who was here with my mother-in-law recently said ‚ÄúNot only is this the best salad I‚Äôve ever had, it‚Äôs also the most beautiful‚Äù. That‚Äôs what I call a compliment. The Chicken Supreme is my favourite cut of chicken, the breast with the succulent wingbone which makes everything juicier. But for dessert I was hesitating. The lady in the drawing and her apples were calling me but I couldn‚Äôt quite put my finger on it. In walks Fabien (he literally walks in many mornings while I&#8217;m still in my pyjamas, to say hi and have coffee). I remember him saying years ago that one of his favourite childhood memories where those of his mother‚Äôs apple fritters (beignets). So that was sorted. As luck would have it, opposite his ch√¢teau is another wine making property with a glorious Kaki tree. Fabien told us he‚Äôd arrange for a permit from the owner to pluck some, he also promised to lend us a ladder. As you can see from the photos, he couldn‚Äôt find a ladder and brought a chair, which was good enough and as my husband would say, more photogenic. (you can see Fabien sitting on that chair next to his sister V√©ronique)</p>
<p>As I‚Äôm writing this I must admit that I‚Äôve missed writing these posts, I‚Äôve missed you all, your comments and thoughts. It‚Äôs a special feeling I don‚Äôt want to ever lose. It also doesn‚Äôt hurt that I‚Äôm drinking Champagne and the kids are behaving. So are the dogs which is even rarer. And my husband is cooking dinner. Spaghetti with garlic an chilies, then pigeon. Then chocolates (he doesn‚Äôt do dessert). It also mean we‚Äôll eat late, that‚Äôs one of his specialities, very late dinners. He recruits the kids, turns it into a game, spends more time selecting music than actually chopping. Then selects the same opera anyway. I‚Äôm not complaining.</p>
<p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/boucherie2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-6562" src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/boucherie2-710x536.jpg" alt="" width="710" height="536" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/boucherie2-710x536.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/boucherie2-300x226.jpg 300w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/boucherie2-768x580.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/montecristo.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-6563" src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/montecristo-710x536.jpg" alt="" width="710" height="536" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/montecristo-710x536.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/montecristo-300x226.jpg 300w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/montecristo-768x580.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/prepjartichokes.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-6564" src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/prepjartichokes-710x536.jpg" alt="" width="710" height="536" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/prepjartichokes-710x536.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/prepjartichokes-300x226.jpg 300w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/prepjartichokes-768x580.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/tourhautcaussan.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-6565" src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/tourhautcaussan-710x473.jpg" alt="" width="710" height="473" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/tourhautcaussan-710x473.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/tourhautcaussan-300x200.jpg 300w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/tourhautcaussan-768x512.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/audreykaki.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-6566" src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/audreykaki-710x536.jpg" alt="" width="710" height="536" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/audreykaki-710x536.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/audreykaki-300x226.jpg 300w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/audreykaki-768x580.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px" /></a></p>
<p><strong>The fairytale</strong></p>
<p>Since last night I‚Äôve been playing around with playlists. Trying to assemble a decent, alternative to the holiday music we always listen to. So far I‚Äôm advancing well. Some French touches ‚Äì Michel Legrand etc. Some all time favourites like Elvis‚Äôs blue Christmas. A lot of sixties music ‚Äì sometimes it feels like Christmas was invented in the sixties. It makes you think of posters of men with hats and pipes, opening the trunks of their Cadillacs and pulling out a box with a puppy in it. A puppy called Buddy, a gift for a boy called Jack. And what is Christmas without the carols? Click <a href="https://open.spotify.com/user/1183644452/playlist/3SLJxdciT0IFsq0FK4iO71">here</a> to follow my playlist on Spotify, it&#8217;s called Mimi&#8217;s Christmas.</p>
<p>This is where I was at until 10 minutes ago, then the phone rang. ‚ÄúWe have found your puppy madame‚Äù said the lady from the veterinary clinic. I was stunned.</p>
<p>In July, our beautiful Moneypenny had a litter of 8 puppies ‚Äì Smooth Fox Terriers. Humfri Bogart, the king of the house is the father. We had 7 boys, all brown and white. One girl, black and white. They had just started going to their new owners when disaster struck in late September. The puppies had been left out later than usual, it was a balmy evening and they were playing under the olive trees and we had a dinner elsewhere with our workshop guests. When we came back one was missing. Nelson. He was the most outgoing, fearless. The handsomest of the lot. Had someone wanted to take a puppy they would have opened the gates and he would always have been the first one to approach. We searched everywhere, Thorir, Oddur &amp; Mathias spent most of the night driving, cycling, walking around the village, the vineyards. Not a trace. For a few days we were hopeful then we just hoped he was fine even if we‚Äôd never see him again.</p>
<p>And now this. A true Christmas miracle. He‚Äôs still at the Vet‚Äôs, it was too late to pick him up tonight as they were closing and my husband wasn‚Äôt here. But tomorrow will be so much fun.</p>
<p>Just like Christmas in the sixties.</p>
<p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/beignets2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-6567" src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/beignets2-710x536.jpg" alt="" width="710" height="536" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/beignets2-710x536.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/beignets2-300x226.jpg 300w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/beignets2-768x580.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/roses.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-6568" src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/roses-710x536.jpg" alt="" width="710" height="536" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/roses-710x536.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/roses-300x226.jpg 300w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/roses-768x580.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px" /></a></p>
