<p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/plumandham.jpg"><img src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/plumandham-710x536.jpg" alt="plumandham" width="710" height="536" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-6421" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/plumandham-710x536.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/plumandham-300x226.jpg 300w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/plumandham-768x580.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/walnuts.jpg"><img src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/walnuts-710x536.jpg" alt="walnuts" width="710" height="536" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-6422" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/walnuts-710x536.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/walnuts-300x226.jpg 300w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/walnuts-768x580.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/cheesewalnutfeuillete.jpg"><img src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/cheesewalnutfeuillete-710x1065.jpg" alt="cheesewalnutfeuillete" width="710" height="1065" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-6427" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/cheesewalnutfeuillete-710x1065.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/cheesewalnutfeuillete-200x300.jpg 200w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/cheesewalnutfeuillete-768x1152.jpg 768w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/cheesewalnutfeuillete.jpg 1512w" sizes="(max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px" /></a></p>
<p><strong>Here are 2 recipes from my new cookbook &#8216;French Country Cooking&#8217;</strong></p>
<p><strong>Comt√©, Ham, and Walnut Feuillet√©</strong><br />
Serves 2</p>
<p>If I were teaching at a French cooking school, this dish would be on the curriculum;<br />
it‚Äôs the perfect crowd-pleaser, and it uses so many wonderful French ingredients.<br />
Take the best cheese and ham you can find. Make a velvety b√©chamel sauce. Add<br />
some moist, tender walnuts just out of the shell. Wrap everything in puff pastry, one<br />
of the most agreeable inventions of French cuisine, and bake it. I knew you‚Äôd like it.</p>
<p>2 tablespoons plus 1 teaspoon / 35 g unsalted butter<br />
3 tablespoons all-purpose flour<br />
¬º teaspoon grated nutmeg<br />
fine sea salt and freshly<br />
ground black pepper<br />
1 cup / 250 ml whole milk<br />
1 shallot, thinly sliced<br />
1/3 cup / 50 g walnuts, chopped<br />
8 ounces / 230 g frozen puff pastry, thawed<br />
1 teaspoon whole-grain mustard<br />
2/3 cup / 100 g grated comt√© cheese<br />
5 ounces / 150 g sliced ham<br />
1 large egg yolk</p>
<p>Preheat the oven to 400 F/200 C. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.</p>
<p>In a small saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of the butter over medium heat. Whisk in the flour until the mixture thickens. Add the nutmeg, season with salt and pepper, and gradually whisk in the milk and simmer, whisking until thickened, up to 5 minutes. Set the b√©chamel sauce aside to cool. </p>
<p>In a saut√© pan, heat the remaining 1 teaspoon butter over medium heat. Add the shallot and cook until slightly golden, about 3 minutes. Add the walnuts and cook for 1 minute more.</p>
<p>Cut the puff pastry into two 9 x 5-inch / 23 x 12.5 cm rectangles. Place one rectangle of pastry on the lined baking sheet. Spread ¬Ω teaspoon of the mustard in a thin layer over the pastry. Spread with one-third of the b√©chamel sauce, half of the cheese, half of the ham, and half of the walnut mixture. Repeat the layering. Finish with a layer of b√©chamel sauce and top with the second pastry rectangle. Seal to the bottom rectangle by pinching together the edges of the pastry.</p>
<p>Beat the egg yolk with a little water and use it to glaze the top with a pastry brush. Using a knife, cut a little round hole in the middle of the pastry to let the steam escape. You can decorate the top with cut pieces of puff pastry (leaves, for example) or lightly score a diamond pattern on top.</p>
<p>Bake the feuillet√© in the oven until golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes. Slice and serve hot.</p>
<p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/mimiinthedark.jpg"><img src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/mimiinthedark-710x536.jpg" alt="mimiinthedark" width="710" height="536" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-6423" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/mimiinthedark-710x536.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/mimiinthedark-300x226.jpg 300w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/mimiinthedark-768x580.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/silvertrays.jpg"><img src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/silvertrays-710x536.jpg" alt="silvertrays" width="710" height="536" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-6424" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/silvertrays-710x536.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/silvertrays-300x226.jpg 300w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/silvertrays-768x580.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/roastchicken2.jpg"><img src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/roastchicken2-710x473.jpg" alt="roastchicken2" width="710" height="473" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-6425" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/roastchicken2-710x473.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/roastchicken2-300x200.jpg 300w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/roastchicken2-768x512.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/roastchicken1.jpg"><img src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/roastchicken1-710x1065.jpg" alt="roastchicken1" width="710" height="1065" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-6426" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/roastchicken1-710x1065.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/roastchicken1-200x300.jpg 200w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/roastchicken1-768x1152.jpg 768w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/roastchicken1.jpg 1512w" sizes="(max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px" /></a></p>
<p><strong>Roast Chicken with Chestnuts and Cabbage</strong></p>
<p>I have a few staple roast chicken recipes that I use all the time. One is simple, with<br />
thyme and lemon; another one is rich, with a lot of cr√®me fra√Æche and delicious<br />
herbs. I didn‚Äôt really need a third one, but I came up with this recipe because I was<br />
looking for something festive, almost like a pheasant or guinea hen‚Äîwhich means<br />
chestnuts, my favorite. Finally, I needed a way to use up all that cabbage that my husband<br />
keeps growing and buying (because he says it‚Äôs the most photogenic vegetable<br />
in the world). This chicken dish is the answer.</p>
<p>For the chicken<br />
1 whole chicken (3 ¬Ω pounds/1.5 kg)<br />
4 tablespoons / 60 g salted butter<br />
fine sea salt and freshly ground black pepper<br />
4 garlic cloves, unpeeled<br />
1 bunch of fresh thyme<br />
1 small onion, halved<br />
1 bay leaf<br />
8 peeled cooked chestnuts (bottled or vacuum-packed)</p>
<p>For the cabbage<br />
1 head savoy cabbage (dark green leaves discarded), cut into 1-inch / 2.5 cm strips<br />
20 ounces / 570 g peeled<br />
cooked chestnuts (bottled or vacuum-packed)<br />
5 tablespoons / 75 g unsalted butter<br />
fine sea salt and freshly ground black pepper<br />
1/3 cup / 80 ml chicken stock<br />
1/3 cup / 80 ml dry white wine</p>
<p>Roast the chicken. Preheat the oven to 350 F / 180 C. Take the chicken out of the refrigerator at least 30 minutes before cooking.</p>
<p>Rub the chicken with the salted butter and season generously both inside and out with salt and pepper. Put the garlic cloves, thyme, onion halves, bay leaf, and chestnuts in the cavity. Put the chicken in a roasting pan and roast for 50 minutes.</p>
<p>Transfer the chicken to a big plate; it will not be fully cooked just yet and will be returned to the oven later, so leave the oven on but increase the temperature to 400 F / 200 C.</p>
<p>Make the cabbage. Keep all the fat and juices in the roasting pan and add the cabbage, chestnuts, and 4 tablespoons / 60 g of the unsalted butter. Season with salt and pepper and toss everything together. Return to the oven and roast for 10 minutes.</p>
<p>Pour in the stock and wine and stir to combine. Brush the chicken with the remaining 1 tablespoon / 15 g butter to gloss the skin and return to the pan. Return the pan to the oven and roast until the chicken is golden brown and cooked through, 10 to 15 minutes.</p>
<p>Let the chicken rest for 15 minutes before serving with the cabbage and chestnuts.</p>
<p><a href="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/cover.jpg"><img src="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/cover-242x300.jpg" alt="cover" width="242" height="300" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-6394" srcset="http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/cover-242x300.jpg 242w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/cover-768x952.jpg 768w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/cover-710x880.jpg 710w, http://4ei1we1252c14dmfxx37crrd.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/cover.jpg 1143w" sizes="(max-width: 242px) 100vw, 242px" /></a></p>

